00:08:19,214 --> 00:08:21,037
So let's start off talking about motivations.

198
00:08:21,477 --> 00:08:24,241
This is a really key part of telling a good story.

199
00:08:25,798 --> 00:08:27,879
So for characters, these are divided between external

200
00:08:28,019 --> 00:08:29,160
and internal motivations.

201
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:32,081
An external motivation is the desire to change something

202
00:08:32,181 --> 00:08:33,361
in the world outside you.

203
00:08:33,962 --> 00:08:36,102
So this is often to get richer,

204
00:08:36,983 --> 00:08:39,084
to steal some money from a bank,

205
00:08:39,164 --> 00:08:41,485
or become rich and famous through doing a particular thing.

206
00:08:41,505 --> 00:08:43,725
That's a very common external motivation.

207
00:08:44,026 --> 00:08:45,706
It changes your status in the outside world.

208
00:08:45,726 --> 00:08:47,247
Another one is to travel.

209
00:08:47,427 --> 00:08:48,947
You want to reach to a certain place,

210
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:50,368
you want to explore a new area.

211
00:08:50,748 --> 00:08:54,510
That's a change in your status in terms of your location.

212
00:08:55,957 --> 00:08:59,019
Forming friendships and love and relationships

213
00:08:59,479 --> 00:09:01,181
is changing your relationship status.

214
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:02,762
It's a status in the outside world.

215
00:09:03,322 --> 00:09:05,163
Emotions are an internal thing in some ways,

216
00:09:05,583 --> 00:09:07,164
but how they affect the outside world

217
00:09:07,244 --> 00:09:08,445
is still an external motivation.

218
00:09:08,865 --> 00:09:11,067
So it could be to date the hot guy in the office,

219
00:09:11,087 --> 00:09:11,687
for example.

220
00:09:12,027 --> 00:09:13,548
That could be the objective of the game

221
00:09:13,849 --> 00:09:14,609
or for your character.

222
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:17,491
So in terms of motivations here,

223
00:09:17,711 --> 00:09:19,632
an internal motivation is a desire

224
00:09:19,652 --> 00:09:21,153
to change something inside the person.

225
00:09:22,195 --> 00:09:26,478
This is usually termed like overcoming a problem, so overcome a block.

226
00:09:26,839 --> 00:09:32,123
It's often an emotional block, overcoming a sense of loneliness, overcoming grief.

227
00:09:33,844 --> 00:09:37,907
Now, revenge is an external thing because you affect revenge on the outside world.

228
00:09:38,308 --> 00:09:40,730
Overcoming grief is the inside part of that.

229
00:09:41,050 --> 00:09:43,672
You try to overcome grief by killing people in the outside world.

230
00:09:44,213 --> 00:09:45,814
That's how a lot of video game plots work.

231
00:09:47,783 --> 00:09:49,847
Another internal motivation is learning something new.

232
00:09:50,187 --> 00:09:52,031
Usually it's something they should have already known.

233
00:09:53,213 --> 00:09:55,498
And you can succeed in one and fail in the other.

234
00:09:56,518 --> 00:09:58,779
And often when you succeed in external motivation

235
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:01,240
and fail in internal motivation, you get a tragedy.

236
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:02,600
That's Romeo and Juliet.

237
00:10:03,260 --> 00:10:05,141
Two families alike in dignity,

238
00:10:05,821 --> 00:10:09,182
who failed to actually ever come to terms

239
00:10:09,262 --> 00:10:11,163
with the fact that they should stop fighting.

240
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:13,763
And their internal necessity

241
00:10:13,823 --> 00:10:15,764
to learn something new about themselves,

242
00:10:15,824 --> 00:10:16,944
to learn that they're all the same,

243
00:10:17,885 --> 00:10:19,585
to learn to accept their differences.

244
00:10:20,645 --> 00:10:23,127
And their failure to do that kills their children.

245
00:10:23,828 --> 00:10:25,229
And that's why that's a tragedy.

246
00:10:25,929 --> 00:10:28,591
So learning something new is a huge thing of an internal change there.

247
00:10:29,852 --> 00:10:33,034
Now both of these things, like I say, they are about change.

248
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,655
A story is always about change.

249
00:10:34,835 --> 00:10:37,357
A story that doesn't have change from beginning to end

250
00:10:37,778 --> 00:10:39,439
is a very, very boring story.

251
00:10:40,439 --> 00:10:42,701
Now it can just be that your character got bigger guns.

252
00:10:43,847 --> 00:10:47,832
It's change of a kind, you know, and it works pretty well, it really does.

253
