551
00:24:05,306 --> 00:24:06,568
So how do we go about doing this?

552
00:24:06,588 --> 00:24:07,969
Well, we do this with scene structure.

553
00:24:08,882 --> 00:24:10,703
This is the final part of that diagram we're going to add in there.

554
00:24:11,284 --> 00:24:16,247
So all scenes on your level must have an objective, which is the player's target goal or experience.

555
00:24:16,928 --> 00:24:20,230
It must have conflict, something that makes the objective more difficult to reach.

556
00:24:21,251 --> 00:24:25,754
This can be either narrative or mechanics or both, some sort of conflict that makes us struggle,

557
00:24:25,854 --> 00:24:27,515
makes it harder for us to make these things happen.

558
00:24:28,036 --> 00:24:31,518
And then an outcome is reached by requiring change from the player or the character.

559
00:24:32,955 --> 00:24:34,936
So they either resolve or adapt to the conflict,

560
00:24:35,276 --> 00:24:37,697
building to the next part of the experience of the story,

561
00:24:37,717 --> 00:24:40,278
and the story goes on with escalating tension there.

